# Patches Lazarus applied during resurrection:
#   - src/dna_io.py: dna_one_hot now calls seq.upper() before one-hot encoding. Previously only uppercase A/C/G/T matched; soft-masked lowercase acgt fell through to the except branch and became all-zero (N) columns, silently zeroing ~half of every repeat-rich sequence. This depressed full-test mean AUROC from the paper's 0.895 down to 0.675. With the fix, clean-encoded sequences reproduce 0.8944.
#   - src/fasta_to_h5.py: new minimal helper to convert an arbitrary FASTA into the HDF5 (test_in: n x 4 x 1 x 600, int8) that basset_predict.lua consumes, enabling label-free single/multi-sequence inference (seq_hdf5.py otherwise requires a targets file).
#   - data/encode_roadmap_test_fixed.h5: benchmark test set (71,886 seqs) re-encoded from the local encode_roadmap.fa with the uppercasing fix (test_out copied unchanged), used to measure the corrected mean AUROC.

